devdoc.author: Andrew Redden - <andrew@groundhog.network>

cancelSubscription(bytes32,bytes).details: Allows to execute a Safe transaction confirmed by required number of owners and then pays the account that submitted the transaction.
cancelSubscription(bytes32,bytes).return: bool hash of on sub to revoke or cancel

cancelSubscriptionAsRecipient(address,ui.details: cancel the subscription as the recipient of the subscription, in cases where a merchant wants to cancel and prevent further payment

changeMasterCopy(address).details: Allows to upgrade the contract. This can only be done via a Safe transaction.

encodeSubscriptionData(address,uint256,b.details: Returns the bytes that are hashed to be signed by owners.

execSubscription(address,uint256,bytes,u.details: Allows to execute a Safe transaction confirmed by required number of owners and then pays the account that submitted the transaction.      Note: The fees are always transferred, even if the user transaction fails.

params.signatures: Packed signature data ({bytes32 r}{bytes32 s}{uint2568 v})

getSubscriptionActionHash(bytes32,string.details: Returns hash to be signed by owners for cancelling a subscription

getSubscriptionHash(address,uint256,byte.details: Returns hash to be signed by owners.

isValidSubscription(bytes32,bytes).details: Allows to execute a Safe transaction confirmed by required number of owners and then pays the account that submitted the transaction.      Note: The fees are always transferred, even if the user transaction fails.

params.subscriptionHash: bytes32 hash of on chain sub

isValidSubscription(bytes32,bytes).return: bool isValid returns the validity of the subscription
